							<a name="tip-88110"></a>
							<div class="KonaBody">
								<div class="tip" tipid="88110" comments="0" rating="8">
									<h2><a href="http://cooking.lifetips.com/tip/88110/cooking-tips/cooking-tips/sticky-situations.html" title="Sticky Situations">Sticky Situations</a></h2>
									<p>Before measuring ingredients such as honey and corn syrup, lightly coat the measuring spoon or cup with vegetable oil. This also works great if you have to measure peanut butter.</p>
